</HEAD><BODY BACKGROUND='Image1.jpg'><H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Sacred Name King James    
Version</H3><P><A HREF='B04C011.htm'>Numbers 11</A></P><CENTER><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>
The Fourth Book of Moses, called Numbers</H2></CENTER><P><A HREF='index.htm'>   
Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5 WIDTH=90%><TR><TD>
</TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 12</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>And Miriam and Aaron spake against Moses because  
of the Ethiopian woman whom he had married: for he had married an Ethiopian     
woman.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>And     
they said, Hath YHVH indeed spoken only by Moses? hath he not spoken also by    
us? And YHVH heard it.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4>    
</TD><TD><P>(Now the man Moses was very meek, above all the men which were upon 
the face of the earth.)</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4>   
</TD><TD><P>And YHVH spake suddenly unto Moses, and unto Aaron, and unto        
Miriam, Come out ye three unto the tabernacle of the congregation. And they     
three came out.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>And YHVH came down in the pillar of the cloud, and stood in the door of the  
tabernacle, and called Aaron and Miriam: and they both came forth.</P></TD></TR>
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6><H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>And he said, Hear now my    
words: If there be a prophet among you, I YHVH will make myself known unto him  
in a vision, and will speak unto him in a dream.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD><P>My servant Moses is not so, who is  
faithful in all mine house.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V8><H4>     
8</H4></TD><TD><P>With him will I speak mouth to mouth, even apparently, and    
not in dark speeches; and the similitude of YHVH shall he behold: wherefore     
then were ye not afraid to speak against my servant Moses?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>And the anger of YHVH was kindled   
against them; and he departed.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V10><H4> 
10</H4></TD><TD><P>And the cloud departed from off the tabernacle; and, behold, 
Miriam became leprous, white as snow: and Aaron looked upon Miriam, and,        
behold, she was leprous.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4>
</TD><TD><P>And Aaron said unto Moses, Alas, my lord, I beseech thee, lay not   
the sin upon us, wherein we have done foolishly, and wherein we have sinned.</P>
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Let her not be  
as one dead, of whom the flesh is half consumed when he cometh out of his       
mother's womb.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>And Moses cried unto YHVH, saying, Heal her now, O EL, I beseech thee.</P>   
</TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH said   
unto Moses, If her father had but spit in her face, should she not be ashamed   
seven days? let her be shut out from the camp seven days, and after that let    
her be received in again.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>      
15</H4></TD><TD><P>And Miriam was shut out from the camp seven days: and the    
people journeyed not till Miriam was brought in again.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>And afterward the people removed  
from Hazeroth, and pitched in the wilderness of Paran.</P></TD></TR></TABLE>    
